However, to tell the truth is not a crime.
In a letter, Mr. Snowden said that he believes that the support of the international community can convince the U.S. government to give up criminal charges against him.
The charges brought by the U.S. Department of Justice include espionage and theft of state property.
Hans-Peter Friedrich, Minister of the Interior of Germany, said Zeit Online: "If Mr. Snowden is ready to talk to German officials, we will find ways to make it possible.
