Mr. Striebele, a member of the parliament of the Green Germany Party, published his photo with Mr. Snowden on Twitter.
During his visit to Russia, he was accompanied by two German journalists.
Mr. Striebele said that, according to the lawyer of the former NSA contract serviceman, Mr. Snowden could not have returned to Russia if he had left.
If Mr. Snowden had given testimony in Germany, he would need guarantees that he would be there, said the MP.
Mr. Snowden said in his letter that he had encountered a scoon and a constant campaign of persecution, which forced him to leave his house.
However, he said that he was inspired by the world's reaction to the political statements.
Citizens around the world, as well as high-ranking officials, including in the United States, considered the exposure of an uncontrolled system of all-theirable surveillance useful for society.
The letter contains a proposal to cooperate with the German authorities, and when the difficulties of this humanitarian situation will be resolved.
