In the U.S. it will be possible to use mobile during the take-off and landing of the aircraft
New rules for the safe use of mobile devices during take-off and landing airliner approved in the United States, according to the BBC.
As expected, American airlines will allow passengers to use smartphones and tablets throughout the flight, the new rules will begin to apply by the end of 2013.
However, communication with the Internet to receive and send e-mail will be prohibited during flights at an altitude of less than 3 kilometers.
Due to the danger of interference with radio equipment of aircraft, cellular voice communication will still be banned.
Thus, passengers of flights will be allowed to read e-books, play games on tablets and other gadgets and watch videos during domestic and international flights.
Before the rules are adopted, airlines will be required to check the safety of the use of electronic devices during the flight.
In addition, airlines will have to convince the U.S. Federal Civil Aviation Administration that they will be able to cope with the alleged impact of mobile on aircraft and aircraft control devices.
According to the source, according to the U.S., in Britain it is also possible to revise the current norms of use of electronic devices in flights.
