Boys - as in girls - puberty comes earlier.
Kaplitz claims that the premise that has the greatest weight is an epidemic of obesity.
In 2001, he helped to study girls from 6 to 9 years, which connects the amount of body fat with puberty.
Other data confirm this conclusion, but there are many other conducive factors.
In this country, African American and Latin American girls tend to reach puberty earlier than their white peers.
There are different explanations.
All over the world, the early puberty seems to be affected by everything: from economic conditions and climate to genes.
